      "comment": "ZIPPING BERKELEY (5) has a strong record this journey here with two wins and a minor from three starts. Was out of the placings last time (30.10) at The Gardens in a Grade 5, finishing fifth and beaten 8 lengths. Looks suited here and rates on top. SLEEK APOLLO (1) turned in a moderate run last time when seventh at Wentworth Park over 520m behind Fantastic Storm (30.60) in a Grade 5. Can do much better this time. IBROX MAVERICK (2) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing third behind Invisible Man (22.90) in a Grade 5. Chased the leaders and with a clean run can be prominent. Must be included in calculations. NOVA REIGN (8) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
